.\" btrdasd(1) man page
.\" Generated from clap CLI definitions in indexer/src/main.rs
.TH BTRDASD 1 "2026-03-05" "0.7.0" "DAS Backup Manager"
.SH NAME
btrdasd \- DAS Backup Manager indexer and orchestrator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B btrdasd
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B btrdasd
(ButteredDASD) manages BTRFS backups to Direct-Attached Storage (DAS).
It provides btrbk orchestration, content indexing with FTS5 full-text search,
health monitoring, schedule management, and backup history tracking.
.PP
Progress messages are printed to stderr so that stdout remains
machine-parseable.
When the global
.B \-\-json
flag is given, all read commands emit JSON output on stdout.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS walk
Index all new snapshots on a backup target.
.PP
.B btrdasd walk
.I TARGET
.RB [ \-\-db
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.I TARGET
Path to backup target mount point.
.TP
.BI \-\-db " PATH"
Path to SQLite database.
Default:
.IR /var/lib/das\-backup/backup\-index.db .
.\"
.SS search
Full-text search across indexed files using FTS5.
.PP
.B btrdasd search
.I QUERY
.RB [ \-\-db
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-limit
.IR N ]
.TP
.I QUERY
FTS5 search query.
Supports prefix matching (e.g.,
.BR report* ).
.TP
.BI \-\-db " PATH"
Path to SQLite database.
Default:
.IR /var/lib/das\-backup/backup\-index.db .
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " N"
Maximum number of results to return.
Default: 50.
.\"
.SS list
List files in a specific snapshot.
.PP
.B btrdasd list
.I SNAPSHOT
.RB [ \-\-db
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.I SNAPSHOT
Snapshot path or name.timestamp pattern.
.TP
.BI \-\-db " PATH"
Path to SQLite database.
Default:
.IR /var/lib/das\-backup/backup\-index.db .
.\"
.SS info
Show database statistics (snapshot count, file count, span count, database size).
.PP
.B btrdasd info
.RB [ \-\-db
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.BI \-\-db " PATH"
Path to SQLite database.
Default:
.IR /var/lib/das\-backup/backup\-index.db .
.\"
.SS setup
Interactive setup wizard \(em configure backup sources, targets, and scheduling.
Requires root privileges.
.PP
.B btrdasd setup
.RB [ \-\-modify ]
.RB [ \-\-upgrade ]
.RB [ \-\-uninstall ]
.RB [ \-\-check ]
.TP
.B \-\-modify
Re-open the wizard with the current configuration pre-filled.
.TP
.B \-\-upgrade
Regenerate all managed files from the existing configuration
(useful after a binary update).
.TP
.B \-\-uninstall
Remove all generated files, disable timers, and optionally remove the database.
.TP
.B \-\-check
Validate the configuration and dependencies, report issues,
but change nothing.
.\"
.SS config dump\-env
Print shell-sourceable KEY=VALUE pairs from the configuration.
.PP
.B btrdasd config dump\-env
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to config.toml.
Default:
.IR /etc/das\-backup/config.toml .
.\"
.SS config show
Pretty-print the current configuration.
.PP
.B btrdasd config show
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to config.toml.
Default:
.IR /etc/das\-backup/config.toml .
.\"
.SS config validate
Validate the configuration and report any issues.
Exits with status 1 if validation errors are found.
.PP
.B btrdasd config validate
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to config.toml.
Default:
.IR /etc/das\-backup/config.toml .
.\"
.SS config edit
Open the configuration file in
.BR $EDITOR
(defaults to
.BR vi ).
.PP
