.RB [ \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to config.toml.
Default:
.IR /etc/das\-backup/config.toml .
.\"
.SS backup run
Run the full backup pipeline: snapshot, send, boot archive, index, and email report.
.PP
.B btrdasd backup run
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-dry\-run ]
.RB [ \-\-full ]
.RB [ \-\-sources
.IR LABELS ]
.RB [ \-\-targets
.IR LABELS ]
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
Path to config.toml.
Default:
.IR /etc/das\-backup/config.toml .
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Preview only \(em do not execute any operations.
.TP
.B \-\-full
Run a full backup instead of incremental.
.TP
.BI \-\-sources " LABELS"
Comma-separated source labels to back up.
Default: all non-manual sources.
.TP
.BI \-\-targets " LABELS"
Comma-separated target labels to send to.
Default: all mounted targets.
.\"
.SS backup snapshot
Create snapshots without sending them to targets.
