.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Produce machine-readable JSON output on all read commands.
This flag is global and may be placed before any subcommand.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful operation.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (backup failure, validation error, missing configuration, etc.).
.SH EXAMPLES
Run a full backup pipeline:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd backup run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Preview a backup without making changes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd backup run \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run a full (non-incremental) backup of specific sources to specific targets:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd backup run \-\-full \-\-sources root,home \-\-targets das\-22tb
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search for files matching a prefix across all indexed snapshots:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd search 'report*'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search with JSON output and limited results:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd \-\-json search 'config' \-\-limit 10
.fi
.RE
.PP
Browse a snapshot directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd restore browse /mnt/backup/root.20260228T030000
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restore specific files from a snapshot:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd restore file /mnt/backup/root.20260228T030000 /tmp/restored etc/fstab etc/btrbk/btrbk.conf
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show drive health and backup status:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd health
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show backup schedule and next run times:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd schedule show
.fi
.RE
.PP
List all configured subvolumes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd subvol list
.fi
.RE
.PP
Index snapshots on a backup target:
.PP
.RS
.nf
btrdasd walk /mnt/backup
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run the interactive setup wizard:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo btrdasd setup
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/das\-backup/backup\-index.db
SQLite database with FTS5 content index and backup history.
.TP
.I /etc/das\-backup/config.toml
Main configuration file for sources, targets, schedule, and email settings.
.TP
.I /etc/btrbk/btrbk.conf
btrbk configuration file (generated by
.B btrdasd setup
from config.toml).
.TP
.I /etc/das\-backup\-email.conf
SMTP credentials for email reports (mode 600).
.TP
.I /var/lib/das\-backup/growth.log
Disk usage growth log for trend monitoring.
